post_text: Installation is complete! Thanks to a great crew this week the playground is completely assembled two days ahead of schedule. Sorry kids, you will still have to wait a few weeks to play on it. We need the concrete to set, then we will install a concrete perimeter, and finally we will install the poured in place rubber surface. It should be ready in approximately three or four weeks!

To All Russia High School band students who sold detergent: Detergent pickup time will be this Friday, 5/22/20 at O'Reilly Machine Tool Services located at 109 Industrial Drive in Russia between 4:00 - 6:00 p.m.
It is the responsibility of the student to pick up their orders and deliver all orders to their customers.
If you are unable to pickup during these hours, please contact Brenda Goubeaux at 937-726-6093 to make other arrangements.
Also, if there are any high school band students that are available help sort all the individual detergent orders starting at 12:30 p.m., we would greatly appreciate it.

post_text:
Detergent Delivery Update from Russia Music Boosters:

We have been receiving weekly updates from the Buckets for Benefit Organization concerning our impending detergent delivery date.

With the recent lifting of restrictions, they have now communicated a possible delivery date for the week of May 18th, but an actual date may not be solidified until possibly next Monday.

We are excited to finally narrow down a delivery timeframe for all our loyal customers and we greatly appreciate your patience during this unfortunate delay.

As we receive updates, we will update everyone and contact the student sellers of all the details for pickup.

Thank you again!

post_text:
Senior Parents and Community Members,

On Tuesday, the Governor announced that HS school graduations were permitted as long as appropriate social distancing rules were followed. The following day he reversed course and said this was no longer an option. I have been in contact with numerous elected officials and Representative Manchester has asked for our help in gathering letters from our local communities that she will present to the Governor and other officials. Attached is a draft letter that you are welcome to use as a reference. We are asking that you please make changes to reflect your personal thoughts and to please email Representative Susan Manchester at rep84@ohiohouse.gov

We want nothing more than to recognize the class of 2020 using a common-sense approach that will ensure the safety of our students and community. Please email representative Manchester and also feel free to share this information with your friends and family as well.

Sincerely,
Steve Rose
Superintendent

post_text:
It is with a sad heart that we announce that all public schools will be closed for the remainder of the 2019-2020 school year. It is also with great disappointment that we announce that there will be no spring sports season. We miss all of our students very much but our hearts especially go out to the graduating class of 2020. In a sign of support for the class of 2020, communities across Ohio are turning on their porch lights from 8:00 - 8:20 PM. Please support our graduating class of 2020 and light up our community for 20 minutes tonight.

Now that this decision has been made, we will continue to provide education in the same format through the end of the traditional school year. â€¦

Dear Parents,

I want to share some updates that we have recently received concerning the current school shutdown due to the COVID-19 virus. Governor DeWine just announced that the school shutdown has been extended through May 1st. Throughout the school shutdown, we will continue with our current plan to continue education services to the district. One change is that 5th grade students will now be receiving a packet as well.

Grades K-5 will be provided packets of instructional materials every two weeks. Parents may pick up the packets for the next two weeks on Friday, April 3rd from 2:00 PM-4:30 PM or Monday, April 6th from 7:30 AM-8:30 AM and 2:00 PM â€“ 4:30 PM. Once again, we willâ€¦

post_text:
At the direction of the Governor of Ohio all schools will be closed starting Tuesday, March 17th through Friday, April 3rd. During this time there will be no extracurricular activities and the school will be closed to the public.

To clarify this starts Tuesday and we will have school on Monday, March 16th.

All staff members will report to work as scheduled during these three weeks and Russia School will transition to a remote classroom at that time. We will work to the best of our ability to continue to provide the best education to our students.

Each student will bring home additional information tomorrow explaining how we will transition to a remote learning environment. Chromebooks will be available for any students in grades 4-8 who may need them. They may be signed out in the office on Monday. We know this is not ideal, but we are trying to make the best out of this very difficult situation. We will keep you informed as new information becomes available.

Russia Local School is installing a new playground the week of June 15th and we are looking for volunteers to help in the construction. Snider Recreation will be leading the project and will be sending a three person crew to supervise and help in the construction process. We are anticipating that the installation will take 4-5 days. Any community member who is interested in assisting with the construction of the project is encouraged to sign up using the link below.

https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1TVY2DSH4IhGlgyAPhTJhkdLHQq0MrWi5dq2yJ7B0vaI/edit?usp=sharing.

A parent must accompany any community member under the age of sixteen. Russia School will be providing lunch and water for all volunteers. Please contact Steve Rose at srose@russiaschool.org if you have any questions.
